OL,7,G1,000 members of the National Union
OL,8,Gof Journalists working at BBC Local
OL,9,Ghave started a 48-hour strike, in
OL,10,Gopposition to cuts to programming and
OL,11,Gstaffing at local radio stations in
OL,12,GEngland.
OL,14,FThe strike is expected to cause
OL,15,Fsignificant disruption to local BBC
OL,16,FTV, radio and online services across
OL,17,FEngland.
OL,19,FA 24-hour strike in March took all
OL,20,Fbut two regional TV services off the
OL,21,Fair and caused significant disruption
OL,22,Fto local radio output.
