PS,c000
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F341A1686118585
OL,7,F"Understandably our members were very
OL,8,Fconcerned about the plans to cut
OL,9,FLocal Radio output, but also about
OL,10,Fthe logistics of outputting extra
OL,11,Fdigital content within the resources
OL,12,Fand systems available. So we
OL,13,Fsubmitted counter proposals, which
OL,14,Fcould have achieved digital and also
OL,15,Fpreserved Local Radio."The counter
OL,16,Fproposals were largely ignored.
OL,17,FAdditional, still 'regional'
OL,18,Fprogrammes, were added to Plan A, but
OL,19,Fdid not restore local content as we
OL,20,Fhad suggested.
OL,3,CLocal BBC TV, radio and online
OL,4,Cservices in England hit by strike
OL,5,Caction
