PS,c000
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F341A1686118585
OL,7,F"Our members were rightly becoming
OL,8,Ffrustrated with the lack of listening
OL,9,Fat the top. By now, a growing body of
OL,10,Fevidence was building up to
OL,11,Fillustrate why this plan was wrong.
OL,12,FSeveral previous senior leaders of
OL,13,FBBC Local Radio stepped in.
OL,15,F"There's been no movement since,
OL,16,Fmeaning we've no choice but to strike
OL,17,Ffor 48 hours next Wednesday and
OL,18,FThursday. The votes of confidence was
OL,19,Fa last resort, with very few other
OL,20,Foptions left.
OL,3,CLocal BBC TV, radio and online
OL,4,Cservices in England hit by strike
OL,5,Caction
